      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The wind slabs of the last few days remain in some cases prone to triggering. They must be evaluated with care and prudence. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular at the base of rock walls, and adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. Avalanches can in many places be released, mostly by large loads. Restraint should be exercised because avalanches can sweep people along and give rise to falls. Backcountry touring calls for meticulous route selection.",
        "highlights": "At elevated altitudes the avalanche prone locations are more prevalent and larger."
